    "details" : {
      "en" : {
        "id" : "en",
        "purpose" : "To assess disease stage and determine recommended treatment strategy for hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) using a Swedish adaptation of the BCLC staging system.",
        "keywords" : [
          "hepatocellular",
          "carcinoma",
          "HCC",
          "BCLC",
          "staging",
          "treatment",
          "liver cancer"
        ],
        "use" : "Use to support structured clinical assessment and treatment planning for patients with suspected or confirmed hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC).\n\nThe guideline is intended for use in adult patients and evaluates the following clinical parameters:\n- Tumour size, number, and distribution\n- Presence of vascular invasion or extrahepatic metastases\n- Liver function assessed by Child–Pugh classification\n- Performance status according to ECOG\n- Presence of cirrhosis\n- Portal vein involvement\n- Eligibility for liver transplantation\n- Presence of severe comorbidity limiting therapy\n- Tumour burden in relation to transplantation criteria\n- Outcome of any tumour downstaging attempt\n\nBased on these inputs, the guideline:\n\nAssigns a disease stage according to a Swedish-modified BCLC framework\n- Early stage\n- Intermediate stage\n- Advanced stage\n- Terminal stage\n\nProvides treatment recommendations, including:\n- Ablation\n- Surgical resection\n- Liver transplantation\n- Transarterial chemoembolization (TACE)\n- Selective internal radiation therapy (SIRT)\n- Systemic oncological treatment\n- Symptom-directed or supportive care\n\nThe output is intended to support, but not replace, multidisciplinary team (MDT) decision-making.",
        "misuse" : "Not to be used for:\n- Staging or treatment planning of non-hepatocellular liver malignancies (e.g. cholangiocarcinoma or liver metastases).\n- Application of the original BCLC algorithm without adaptation to Swedish clinical practice.\n- Independent clinical decision-making without multidisciplinary evaluation.\n- Prognostic estimation without consideration of clinical factors not captured by the guideline.",
        "copyright" : "© Cambio CDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details" : {
      "references" : "Regionala cancercentrum i samverkan. Nationellt vårdprogram levercellscancer: Kapitel 8 Diagnostik och staging. Kunskapsbanken, 2024. Available at: https://kunskapsbanken.cancercentrum.se/diagnoser/levercellscancer/vardprogram/diagnostik/",
      "en" : "A structured clinical decision support guideline used to assess disease stage and recommend treatment strategies for hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) based on the Swedish adaptation of the Barcelona Clinic Liver Cancer (BCLC) staging system."
    }
  },
